# Deploy-time secrets/config for small-messanger's Hormiga prod footprint.
# Copy to deploy/.env (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit real values.

# --- coturn (TURN/STUN for WebRTC) ---------------------------------------
# Long-term credential mechanism (--lt-cred-mech --user=USER:PASSWORD).
# The live host currently runs demo-grade user:pass — ROTATE for real use.
TURN_USER=
TURN_PASSWORD=
TURN_REALM=hormi.isolutions.io
TURN_EXTERNAL_IP=91.99.6.25
# If you switch coturn to the shared-secret mechanism (--use-auth-secret),
# supply TURN_SECRET instead of TURN_USER/TURN_PASSWORD and adjust the compose.
# TURN_SECRET=

# --- messenger admin key (X-Admin-Key) -----------------------------------
# The MESSENGER admin key that guards our messenger's admin/service HTTP
# endpoints (e.g. POST /api/chats provisioning). This is the value of
# `hormiga.admin.key` on the messenger backend (currently "81b2…").
# It is DISTINCT from the IDS/kratosgate admin key (IDS_ADMIN_KEY, "be6fa…").
# See DEPLOYMENT-CHANGES.md for the frontend single-key collision caveat.
MESSENGER_ADMIN_KEY=

# The IDS/kratosgate admin key used for /ids/admin/users lookups. This one is
# current/valid on the host; supply it if you rebuild the frontend bundle.
# VITE_IDS_ADMIN_KEY=

# --- SPA deploy target (see ../deploy.sh) --------------------------------
DEPLOY_HOST=den@91.99.6.25
